the Virgin Mary, mother of Jesus Christ
a person who has no experience of a particular activity

simple_means.memory_skill: vir 男人 + gin → 处女，处男

tr: a person who has never had sex
in a state of sexual virginity
example: men have decreed that their women must be pure and virginal

tr: being used or worked for the first time

value.def: A virgin is someone who has never had sex.

example.ex: I was a virgin until I was thirty years old...
They were both virgins when they met and married.
example.tran: 他们从相识到结婚前都未曾经历男女之事。

value.def: You use virgin to describe something such as land that has never been used or spoiled.

example.ex: Within 40 years there will be no virgin forest left.
example.tran: 过不了40年，就将不会再有未开发的森林了。

value.def: If you say that a situation is virgin territory, you mean that you have no experience of it and it is completely new for you.
value.tran: 陌生的情形;全新的领域

value.def: You can use virgin to describe someone who has never done or used a particular thing before.

example.ex: Until he appeared in 'In the Line of Fire' Malkovich had been an action-movie virgin...
example.tran: 出演《火线狙击》以前，马尔科维奇从未演过动作片。

example.ex: He was a political virgin when Mrs Thatcher picked him as Lord Advocate.
example.tran: 当撒切尔夫人任命他为苏格兰检察总长时，他是个完全没有从政经验的新人。

value.tran: 新手;雏儿；完全无经验的人

trans: 陌生的情形;全新的领域
